1
00:03:44,320 --> 00:03:47,250
This is unbelievable!
Look at this!

2
00:03:47,300 --> 00:03:50,310
There's no city like this in the world.
There never was!

3
00:03:50,340 --> 00:03:52,640
You act like you've never been here before.

4
00:03:52,660 --> 00:03:55,500
I don't get here often enough.
That's the problem.

5
00:03:55,510 --> 00:03:59,790
Can you picture how drop-dead
gorgeous this city is in the rain?

6
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:03,120
Imagine this town in the '20s.
Paris in the '20s,

7
00:04:03,150 --> 00:04:05,470
in the rain; the artists and writers.

8
00:04:05,470 --> 00:04:07,630
Why does every city have to be in the rain?

9
00:04:07,670 --> 00:04:10,050
What's wonderful about getting wet?

10
00:04:10,050 --> 00:04:13,710
I mean, could you ever picture us
moving here after we're married?

11
00:04:13,770 --> 00:04:15,370
Oh God, no.

12
00:04:15,410 --> 00:04:17,610
I could never live out of the United States.

13
00:04:17,680 --> 00:04:20,380
You know, if I'd stayed here and written novels,

14
00:04:20,380 --> 00:04:25,870
and not gotten, you know, caught up in that,
just, grinding out movie scripts...

15
00:04:25,880 --> 00:04:26,650
I'll tell you something:

16
00:04:26,650 --> 00:04:29,020
I would drop the house in Beverly Hills,

17
00:04:29,020 --> 00:04:32,000
the pool, everything,
in a second.

18
00:04:32,190 --> 00:04:34,510
I mean, look:
This is where Monet lived and painted.

19
00:04:34,510 --> 00:04:36,510
We're 30 minutes from town.

20
00:04:36,530 --> 00:04:38,510
Imagine the two of us settling here.

21
00:04:38,510 --> 00:04:42,040
We could do it, I mean,
if my book turns out.

22
00:04:43,150 --> 00:04:44,630
You're in love with a fantasy.

23
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:47,320
I'm in love with you.

24
00:04:51,610 --> 00:04:54,270
We should get back to town.
We're meeting Mom and Dad for dinner.

25
00:04:54,300 --> 00:04:55,510
Let's meet 'em.

26
00:05:01,780 --> 00:05:03,540
<i>There are our sightseers.</i>

27
00:05:03,570 --> 00:05:07,140
If I never see another charming
boulevard or bistro again, I...

28
00:05:07,140 --> 00:05:09,490
- What a town!
- Yes. To visit.

29
00:05:09,490 --> 00:05:11,090
I could see myself living here!

30
00:05:11,090 --> 00:05:13,110
I feel like the Parisians kind of "get me."

31
00:05:13,110 --> 00:05:16,310
I can see myself just strolling
along the Left Bank with a,

32
00:05:16,440 --> 00:05:18,250
you know, baguette under my arm,

33
00:05:18,250 --> 00:05:21,920
headed to Café de Flore
to scribble away on my book.

34
00:05:21,930 --> 00:05:24,730
What did Hemingway say?
He called it a "moveable feast."

35
00:05:24,740 --> 00:05:27,510
In this traffic, nothing moves.

36
00:05:27,580 --> 00:05:31,020
Well, a toast to John's new business venture here!

37
00:05:31,330 --> 00:05:32,790
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

38
00:05:33,250 --> 00:05:36,080
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

39
00:05:36,220 --> 00:05:38,430
Well, I'll be perfectly frank.

40
00:05:38,430 --> 00:05:44,220
I'm excited about this corporate merger between
our folks and the French company, but otherwise,

41
