(No, no. I speak very well. Absolutely. You want to see?)

1275
01:19:42,320 --> 01:19:45,890
Degas and I were just
talking about how this...

1276
01:19:45,890 --> 01:19:51,320
um...this...<i>cette...génération est plus vide, et il manque d'imagination.</i>
(...this generation is empty, and is missing imagination.)

1277
01:19:51,700 --> 01:19:53,680
He said...He says that

1278
01:19:53,680 --> 01:19:58,070
this generation is empty,
and has no imagination.

1279
01:19:58,330 --> 01:20:02,310
Better to have lived during the...
<i>la Renaissance</i>.

1280
01:20:02,310 --> 01:20:05,440
No! This is the golden age.

1281
01:20:05,440 --> 01:20:07,000
- Non.
- <i>C'est l'âge d'or!</i>(It's the golden age!)

1282
01:20:07,000 --> 01:20:09,930
<i>Pas de tout. La Renaissance, c'est beaucoup mieux.</i>
(Not at all. The Renaissance is much better.)

1283
01:20:11,020 --> 01:20:13,090
<i>Qu'est-ce que vous faites dans la vie?</i>
(What is it you do?)

1284
01:20:13,090 --> 01:20:15,610
<i>J'étudie la haute-couture.</i>
(I study high fashion.)

1285
01:20:15,610 --> 01:20:17,850
<i>C'est pour ça vous êtes ****</i>(That's why you're dressed like that.)

1286
01:20:19,420 --> 01:20:21,360
<i>Je comprends maintenant!</i>
(I understand now!)

1287
01:20:21,360 --> 01:20:23,360
<i>Les vêtements tres jeune.</i>
(The youthful clothes.)

1288
01:20:24,000 --> 01:20:26,640
<i>Voulez vous de lui présenter à Richard?</i>
(Would you introduce her to Richard?)

1289
01:20:26,640 --> 01:20:31,120
- <i>Ah, oui!</i> (Oh, yes!)
