1290
01:20:31,120 --> 01:20:34,620
He's looking for someone
to do costumes for the new ballet.

1291
01:20:34,620 --> 01:20:36,170
So, <i>vous intéresse</i>?
(So, you're interested?)

1292
01:20:36,170 --> 01:20:38,170
- Ballet costumes?
- Yes.

1293
01:20:38,170 --> 01:20:39,980
Oh my God! I...

1294
01:20:39,980 --> 01:20:42,080
I don't live here.

1295
01:20:42,080 --> 01:20:43,890
I mean, I do, but I don't. I...

1296
01:20:43,890 --> 01:20:46,030
It's best not to go
into too many details. We're...

1297
01:20:46,110 --> 01:20:49,000
We're temporarily
passing through.

1298
01:20:50,290 --> 01:20:52,770
Can I speak with you a minute?

1299
01:20:54,770 --> 01:20:56,770
<i>Permitée</i>?
(May I?)

1300
01:20:57,850 --> 01:20:59,610
<i>Enchanté.</i>.

1301
01:21:00,690 --> 01:21:03,980
Wow, it didn't take
Gaugin long to start steaming in.

1302
01:21:03,980 --> 01:21:06,140
Let's never go back to the '20s!

1303
01:21:06,140 --> 01:21:08,140
- What are you talking about?
- We should stay here.

1304
01:21:08,140 --> 01:21:10,710
It's the start of La Belle Époque!

1305
01:21:10,720 --> 01:21:15,500
It's the greatest, most
beautiful era Paris has ever known.

1306
01:21:15,500 --> 01:21:19,460
Yeah, but about the '20s,
and the Charleston,

1307
01:21:19,460 --> 01:21:21,460
and the Fitzgeralds,
and the Hemingways?

1308
01:21:21,460 --> 01:21:23,800
I mean, I love those guys.

1309
01:21:24,080 --> 01:21:27,840
But it's the present.
It's dull.

1310
01:21:28,540 --> 01:21:30,170
Dull?

1311
01:21:30,520 --> 01:21:32,550
It's not my present.

1312
01:21:32,550 --> 01:21:34,890
I'm from 2010.

1313
01:21:37,850 --> 01:21:39,430
What do you mean?

1314
01:21:39,430 --> 01:21:43,850
I dropped in on you the same way
we're dropping in on the 1890s.

1315
01:21:44,960 --> 01:21:46,240
You did?

1316
01:21:46,240 --> 01:21:49,700
I was trying to escape my present
the same way you're trying to escape yours,

1317
01:21:49,700 --> 01:21:51,860
to a golden age.

1318
01:21:53,030 --> 01:21:56,850
Surely you don't think
the '20s are a golden age!

1319
01:21:56,850 --> 01:21:59,300
Well, yeah. To me they are.

1320
01:21:59,300 --> 01:22:03,650
But I'm from the '20s, and I'm
telling you the golden age is La Belle Époque.

1321
01:22:03,650 --> 01:22:09,070
And look at these guys. I mean, to them,
their golden age was the Renaissance.

1322
01:22:09,070 --> 01:22:13,530
You know, they're trade <i>Belle Époque</i>
to be painting alongside

